
=  Pablo Solón is the Executive Director of [[Focus on the Global South]]


=Bio=

'''1.'''

Executive Director of Focus on the Global South. As Bolivian Ambassador to the UN, he spearheaded successful resolutions on the Human Right to Water, International Mother Earth Day, Harmony with Nature, and the Rights of Indigenous Peoples. He was the chief negotiator for Climate Change of Bolivia and helped organize the World People's Conference on Climate Change and Mother Earth Rights in 2010. 
"Pablo Solon was formerly the ambassador to the United Nations from the Plurinational state of Bolivia and has been a strong advocate for the Rights of Nature.


'''2.'''


Solón has had extensive involvement in the global justice movement over the years, including social activism in indigenous movements, workers’ unions, student associations and human rights and cultural organizations in his native Bolivia."
(http://climate-connections.org/2012/04/17/news-bulletin-pablo-solon-named-executive-director-of-focus-on-the-global-south/)


